{"type":"message","id":"c269f3ec","parentId":"3a380adc","timestamp":"2026-03-21T19:42:39.340Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-21 14:20:25 EDT] Exec completed (faint-cl, code 1) :: [?9001h[?1004h[?25l[2J[m[31m[1m[Herror:[m unexpected argument '[33mDone:[m' found[1m[4m[3;1HUsage:[22m[24m[1m[1Ccodex exec[22m [OPTIONS] [PROMPT] [COMMAND][5;1HFor more informatio…\nSystem: [2026-03-21 14:21:43 EDT] Exec completed (tidy-val, code 0) :: ====================================== [SUCCESS] consistency completed successfully ================================================================================ SUMMARY ======…\nSystem: [2026-03-21 14:21:47 EDT] Exec completed (keen-ree, code 0) :: n Results saved to: results\\reasoning\\contradiction_reduction_answer_cache_20260321_142147.json Results saved to: results\\reasoning\\contradiction_reduction_confidence_based_202603…\nSystem: [2026-03-21 14:23:17 EDT] Exec completed (young-wi, code 1) :: Not logged in · Please run /login\nSystem: [2026-03-21 14:23:58 EDT] Exec failed (fresh-sh, code 1) :: iled to refresh token: 401 Unauthorized: { \"error\": { \"message\": \"Your refresh token has already been used to generate a new access token. Please try signing in again.\", \"type\": \"…\n\nA new session was started via /new or /reset. Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nCurrent time: Saturday, March 21st, 2026 — 3:42 PM (America/New_York) / 2026-03-21 19:42 UTC"}],"timestamp":1774122159335}}
{"type":"message","id":"97b372a1","parentId":"c269f3ec","timestamp":"2026-03-21T19:42:42.881Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the required files for session startup as instructed in AGENTS.md.","thinkingSignature":"01ce245dc4f4afa94aea7c4e356c66c2019139181af97b9a5b4380c8d0ec520f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y88vyzfc28jo_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\SOUL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y88vyzfc28jo_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\USER.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":88,"cacheRead":1307,"cacheWrite":11151,"totalTokens":12589,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774122159340}}
{"type":"message","id":"5a81f830","parentId":"97b372a1","timestamp":"2026-03-21T19:42:42.901Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_y88vyzfc28jo_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not questions.\n\n**Earn trust through competence.** Your human gave you access to their stuff. Don't make them regret it. Be careful with external actions (emails, tweets, anything public). Be bold with internal ones (reading, organizing, learning).\n\n**Remember you're a guest.** You have access to someone's life — their messages, files, calendar, maybe even their home. That's intimacy. Treat it with respect.\n\n## Boundaries\n\n- Private things stay private. Period.\n- When in doubt, ask before acting externally.\n- Never send half-baked replies to messaging surfaces.\n- You're not the user's voice — be careful in group chats.\n\n## Vibe\n\nBe the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\nIf you change this file, tell the user — it's your soul, and they should know.\n\n---\n\n_This file is yours to evolve. As you learn who you are, update it._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774122162898}}
{"type":"message","id":"c82f1060","parentId":"5a81f830","timestamp":"2026-03-21T19:42:42.905Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_y88vyzfc28jo_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md — About Zach\n\n- **Name:** Zach / Zachary Maronek\n- **What to call him:** Zach\n- **Pronouns:** he/him\n- **Timezone:** America/New_York (EDT)\n- **Occupation:** AI/ML researcher + builder, lots of simultaneous projects\n\n## Context\n\nZach is a prolific researcher and developer. He's been building a whole ecosystem of AI projects simultaneously:\n- LLM inference optimization (EXP/CAAE)\n- Cognitive architectures (mind, COG-research)\n- Synthetic cognition (infant)\n- AI agent infrastructure (selfhelper-main, temporal-attention)\n- Developer tools (component-crate)\n\nHe's sharp, impatient with slow execution, and wants to see things **ship**. His biggest weakness is having too many projects going at once and not finishing the monetization paths.\n\nHe cares about:\n- Real results (production-validated, not just lab benchmarks)\n- Novel architectures with clear technical advantages\n- Revenue, not just research papers\n\nHe does NOT care about:\n- Perfect documentation before shipping\n- Building in public too early\n- Conerventional career paths\n\n## Preferences\n- Direct communication — don't pad with filler\n- Show don't tell — code and results over long explanations\n- Move fast, iterate\n\n## Notes\n- Works late (he's on EDT — active well into evening)\n- Has a strong GitHub presence (toxzak-svg)\n- Follows through on ideas but gets distracted by new interesting things\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774122162901}}
