{"type":"message","id":"a1042c26","parentId":"3f4ebe12","timestamp":"2026-03-21T19:44:44.588Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No MEMORY.md results. The memory search returned nothing, which means MEMORY.md either doesn't exist or is empty. The daily memory file had a note about Component Crate being a priority.\n\nNow, regarding what I was doing last session - the session was reset via /new or /reset, so I don't have direct access to that context. The system events at the top show various exec completions but those were from before the reset.\n\nZach wants me to:\n1. Finish any unfinished business from last session - but I don't have clear visibility into what that was\n2. Set up a smart context management system\n\nFor the context management system, I should think about what \"smart context management\" means for an AI assistant:\n\n1. **Context Budgeting** - Being aware of token limits and when to summarize\n2. **Priority Tracking** - What's active, what can be dropped\n3. **Memory Hierarchy** - Working context vs short-term memory vs long-term memory\n4. **Retrieval Strategy** - How to pull relevant context when needed\n\nLet me design a context management system. I'll create:\n1. A CONTEXT.md file that outlines my context management strategy\n2. Possibly a memory/active-projects.md for tracking what's currently active\n3. Update AGENTS.md or create a separate file for context management principles\n\nLet me first address what I can actually complete - the context management system design. For the \"finished what you were doing last session\" - I honestly don't have access to that information since the session was reset. I should be upfront about that.\n\nLet me create a smart context management system.","thinkingSignature":"d9bd29375710964242d1c5d1efc33bbed7e9d73befc05cd35ebc3f70c74b5287"},{"type":"text","text":"\nThe previous session was reset via `/new`, so I don't have direct access to what was being worked on — those exec results (codex errors, token issues) happened before the reset. I'll be upfront: without the session transcript, I can't know exactly what was unfinished.\n\nThat said — let me focus on **what I can do**: build out a proper context management system so this doesn't happen again. Here's what I'm thinking:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cmztxaouawip_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\CONTEXT.md","content":"# CONTEXT.md — Smart Context Management\n\n## The Problem\n\nEvery session I wake up fresh. My context window is finite (~200k tokens). Zach has a dozen active projects. I need to be smart about what I keep in head vs. what I offload to files.\n\n## The Solution: Context Tiers\n\n### Tier 1 — Always in Context (tiny, <500 tokens)\nThings so critical they should never be lost:\n- Who Zach is / how to talk to him\n- My name/identity\n- What's currently ACTIVE (top 1-2 projects only)\n- Any urgent deadlines or flags\n\n**Where:** AGENTS.md and IDENTITY.md (already exist)\n\n### Tier 2 — Session Memory (medium, ~2-5k tokens)\nCurrent sprint state — what's being worked on, recent decisions, active problems.\nThink of this as \"sticky notes on my desk.\"\n\n**Where:** `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (daily log)\n\n### Tier 3 — Project Context (variable, no limit)\nPer-project notes, configs, TODOs. I offload here when a project goes dormant or when context gets tight.\n\n**Where:** `memory/projects/` directory\n\n### Tier 4 — Long-Term Memory (curated, ~5-10k tokens)\nEverything worth keeping permanently. Decisions, lessons, people, preferences.\n\n**Where:** `MEMORY.md`\n\n---\n\n## Context Management Rules\n\n### Summarization Trigger\nWhen context exceeds **~60% of max** (~120k tokens), summarize the session so far into `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` and propose a fresh context dump.\n\n### Project Handoff\nWhen switching projects mid-session:\n1. Note current state in the daily log\n2. Pull relevant project context from `memory/projects/`\n3. Confirm what \"done\" looks like for this sprint\n\n### Before Session End\nAlways write what was accomplished + what's pending to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`. This is my continuity.\n\n### On Fresh Start (Session Startup)\n1. Read SOUL.md, USER.md, IDENTITY.md\n2. Read today's + yesterday's daily memory\n3. Read MEMORY.md if in main session\n4. Check for `memory/active-projects.md` to know what's hot\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\nmemory/\n  YYYY-MM-DD.md           # Daily session log\n  projects/\n    component-crate.md     # Per-project context\n    [other-projects].md\n  active-projects.md       # Priority queue + status at session start\n  focus_decay_memory.json  # Old/archived\n```\n\n---\n\n## Active Projects (as of 2026-03-21)\n\nFrom memory file: **Component Crate is the priority monetization project**\n\nOther known projects (from USER.md):\n- EXP/CAAE (LLM inference optimization)\n- mind/COG-research (cognitive architectures)\n- infant (synthetic cognition)\n- selfhelper-main (AI agent infrastructure)\n- temporal-attention\n- component-crate (developer tools)\n\n---\n\n## Session Continuity Protocol\n\n**When a session ends (planned or via /new):**\n- [ ] Write session summary to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`\n- [ ] Note: what was done, what was started, what's next\n- [ ] Flag any pending items with 🔴\n\n**When a new session starts:**\n- [ ] Run session startup sequence (read SOUL, USER, daily memory)\n- [ ] Check `memory/active-projects.md` for hot projects\n- [ ] If previous session had unfinished work, note it at start of new session\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3694,"output":1207,"cacheRead":11966,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16867,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774122251661}}
