ram.groupAllowFrom or                 |\n|    channels.telegram.allowFrom, or set groupPolicy to \"open\".            |\n|                                                                          |\n+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+\nService: Scheduled Task (registered)\nFile logs: \\tmp\\openclaw\\openclaw-2026-03-21.log\n\nConfig (cli): ~\\.openclaw\\openclaw.json\nConfig (service): ~\\.openclaw\\openclaw.json\n\nGateway: bind=loopback (127.0.0.1), port=18789 (env/config)\nProbe target: ws://127.0.0.1:18789\nDashboard: http://127.0.0.1:18789/\nProbe note: Loopback-only gateway; only local clients can connect.\n\nRuntime: unknown (state Ready, last run time 3/21/2026 12:52:33 PM, Task status is locale-dependent and no numeric Last Run Result was available.)\nRPC probe: ok\n\nListening: 127.0.0.1:18789\nTroubles: run openclaw status\nTroubleshooting: https://docs.openclaw.ai/troubleshooting\n","name":"openclaw gateway"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774122699963}}
{"type":"message","id":"1bdfa6cb","parentId":"4f4840be","timestamp":"2026-03-21T19:51:44.475Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway is running and RPC is OK. But there's a Telegram warning: `channels.telegram.groupPolicy is \"allowlist\" but groupAllowFrom (and allowFrom) is empty — all group messages will be silently dropped.`\n\nThis means Telegram is configured but the group allowlist is empty. This isn't a \"is it working\" question but rather a configuration issue if Zach wants to use group chats.\n\nLet me check if Telegram is actually connected/working by looking at the channels config.","thinkingSignature":"1f53b8637e0bf1e3e596e477a7fcdd814ab9e3b961bb194e4503900e4841b095"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ailnb6wapk8y_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw status 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":21583,"output":131,"cacheRead":11966,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33680,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774122699968}}
