{"type":"message","id":"5f7f41b5","parentId":"05daad9a","timestamp":"2026-03-21T20:36:51.208Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No pending requests now, but earlier there was one from Ton0Fun. Let me check the allowFrom config - it might need to be updated to allow Zach's Telegram ID. Let me also check what the pairing workflow is.\n\nFrom the earlier log:\n```\n2026-03-21T15:00:39.645-04:00 info {\"module\":\"telegram-auto-reply\"} {\"chatId\":\"8371302588\",\"senderUserId\":\"8371302588\",\"username\":\"Ton0Fun\",\"firstName\":\"Ton0Fun\",\"matchKey\":\"none\",\"matchSource\":\"none\"} telegram pairing request\n```\n\nThe pairing request was from Ton0Fun with chatId 8371302588. Maybe it was auto-approved or it expired?\n\nLet me ask Zach what Telegram account he's using. The issue is the dmPolicy is \"pairing\" which means unknown senders need to be approved. If Zach's Telegram account wasn't in the pairing request, he needs to either:\n1. Approve his own pairing request if it was pending\n2. Change dmPolicy to \"open\" \n3. Add his Telegram ID to allowFrom\n\nLet me check the config again to see if there's an allowFrom list.","thinkingSignature":"c6c18e1e350851e2a85a59510b217e02efb93831d229beeeeff853e76bbdaeec"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_q8yd2rw65wri_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw pairing --help 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":33732,"output":281,"cacheRead":11966,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45979,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774125403269}}
